in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F23142706%2F5553604787_a38f04d388_k1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Amidst%20strained%20relations%2C%20India%20urged%20Canada%20during%20the%20review%20of%20its%20human%20rights%20record%20at%20the%20UNHRC%20to%20boost%20its%20legal%20framework%20to%20stop%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmisuse%E2%80%9D%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression%20to%20incite%20violence%20and%20prevent%20activities%20of%20extremist%20groups.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20call%20by%20India%20was%20presented%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Universal%20Periodic%20Review%20(UPR)%20process%2C%20under%20which%20member%20states%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20undergo%20a%20periodic%20evaluation%20of%20their%20human%20rights%20records%20conducted%20by%20the%2047%20members%20of%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20in%20Geneva.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2010%2C%20Canada%20underwent%20the%20UPR%20process%20for%20the%20fourth%20time%2C%20receiving%20evaluations%20from%20the%20UPR%20working%20group%2C%20consisting%20of%20all%20UNHRC%20members.%20Canada%20was%20among%20the%2014%20countries%20reviewed%20during%20the%20current%20session.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20offered%20three%20suggestions%20to%20Canada%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20spirit%20of%20constructive%20dialogue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COne%2C%20further%20strengthen%20the%20domestic%20framework%20to%20prevent%20misuse%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression%20for%20inciting%20violence%20and%20disallow%20activities%20of%20groups%20which%20are%20promoting%20extremism%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.un.org%2Fen%2Fasset%2Fk14%2Fk14bhl5fi4%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%20Indian%20diplomat%20Mohammed%20Hussain%20K.S%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20called%20on%20Canada%20to%20%E2%80%9Ceffectively%20prevent%20attacks%20on%20places%20of%20worships%20of%20religious%20and%20racial%20minorities%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cstrengthen%20legislative%20and%20other%20measures%20to%20address%20hate%20crimes%20and%20hate%20speech%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThird%2C%20put%20an%20end%20to%20structural%20discrimination%20against%20children%20belonging%20to%20indigenous%20groups.%20And%20address%20disparities%20in%20access%20to%20services%20by%20all%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20the%20Indian%20representative.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20publicly%20accused%20India%20of%20being%20involved%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20a%20Sikh%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20relations%20have%20gone%20into%20deep%20freeze.%20Both%20countries%20expelled%20a%20diplomat%20in%20a%20tit-for-tat%20move%2C%20with%20India%20taking%20additional%20measures%20of%20halting%20visa%20services%20for%20all%20Canadian%20nationals.%20New%20Delhi%20further%20insisted%20on%20diplomatic%20parity%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20departure%20of%2041%20Canadian%20diplomats%20from%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20has%20vehemently%20rejected%20the%20allegations%20as%20%E2%80%9Cabsurd%E2%80%9D%20and%20asked%20for%20Canada%20to%20share%20the%20evidence.%20Indian%20officials%20have%20also%20complained%20that%20Canada%20does%20not%20take%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20about%20activities%20of%20Khalistani%20separatists%20seriously.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fpolitics%2Farticle-india-envoy-tells-ottawa-to-produce-evidence-that-new-delhi-was-behind%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20recent%20interview%20with%20a%20Canadian%20newspaper%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20high%20commissioner%20to%20Ottawa%2C%20Sanjay%20Kumar%20Varma%20said%20that%20there%20had%20been%20no%20action%20taken%20on%2026%20requests%20made%20to%20Canada%20to%20extradite%20people%20to%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20had%20especially%20umbrage%20at%20the%20posters%20and%20banners%20put%20up%20by%20Khalistani%20groups%20in%20Canada%20that%20specifically%20targeted%20Indian%20diplomats.%20Canadian%20officials%20had%2C%20however%2C%20expressed%20their%20inability%20to%20put%20charges%20because%20the%20language%20used%20in%20those%20posters%20had%20been%20within%20the%20legal%20threshold%20of%20permissibility.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2010%2C%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra%20claimed%20that%20India%20had%20%E2%80%9Ccore%20security%20concerns%E2%80%9D%20after%20the%20United%20States%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Anthony%20Blinken%20again%20asked%20New%20Delhi%20to%20join%20the%20Canadian%20investigation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20previous%20UPR%20cycle%20that%20Canada%20underwent%20in%202018%2C%20India%20put%20forth%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmindiaun.gov.in%2Fpageinfo%2FMTY1Mw%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esix%20recommendations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20had%20also%20included%20calling%20for%20prevention%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmisuse%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cglorify%5Bing%5D%20terrorists%20as%20martyrs%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699765135000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F23142706%2F5553604787_a38f04d388_k1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Funhrc-india-canada-universal-periodic-review%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Member%20states%20of%20the%20UN%20undergo%20a%20periodic%20evaluation%20of%20their%20human%20rights%20records%20by%20the%2047%20members%20of%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20in%20Geneva.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A31%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Funhrc-india-canada-universal