the%20far%20off%20Burma%20(present-day%20Myanmar)%20in%201945.%20Amid%20bombings%2C%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20armed%20force%20remained%20adamant%20as%20they%20sang%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EKadam%20Kadam%20Badhaye%20Ja%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20the%20regimental%20quick%20march%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20regiment%20managed%20to%20reach%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Irrawaddy%20River%20%E2%80%94%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20largest%20river%20and%20most%20important%20commercial%20waterway%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20flooded.%20This%20made%20it%20impossible%20for%20them%20to%20cross%20the%20river%20and%20join%20the%20major%20INA%20army%20on%20the%20other%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20regiment%20set%20their%20camps%20on%20the%20bank.%20However%2C%20they%20were%20attacked%20by%20the%20British%20and%20put%20behind%20bars%20for%20over%20a%20month.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20were%20forced%20to%20retreat%20to%20Bangkok.%20While%20all%20the%20other%20women%20went%20back%20to%20their%20homes%2C%20%3Cem%3Edadi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(grandma)%20had%20nowhere%20to%20go.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20her%20father%2C%20who%20was%20out%20on%20a%20secret%20mission%2C%20was%20put%20in%20a%20Singapore%20jail.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20news%20of%20the%20atomic%20bombings%20in%20Japan%20surfaced%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%201945%2C%20Hiroshima%20and%20Nagasaki%20were%20bombed%20with%20nuclear%20weapons%20and%20the%20Japanese%20forces%20were%20forced%20to%20surrender.%20Two%20weeks%20later%2C%20on%2018%20August%201945%2C%20the%20plane%20carrying%20Netaji%2C%20who%20was%20on%20his%20way%20to%20Tokyo%2C%20crashed.%20This%20came%20as%20a%20defeat%20for%20the%20Indian%20National%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fasha-san-5-1699625115